CALENDAR, HEBREW AND JEWISH. See

Day, the Hebrew;  Moon, Semitic Conceptions of; 
 Year, the Hebrew; 
 Synagogue.

The story of the worship of the golden calf during 
the desert journey is given Ex. xxxii. and
Deuteronomy ix. 7–21; cf. 
Neh. ix. 18; 
Ps. cvi. 19–20;
Acts vii. 39–40. The authorized calf-worship of
Northern Israel is mentioned I Kings xii. 28–33;
II Kings x. 29, 
xvii. 16; 
Hos. viii. 5–6, 
x. 5–6, 
xiii. 2; 
II Chron. xi. 15, 
xiii. 8. The Hebrew term
generally applied to the calf is ‘egel; ‘eglah in 
Hos. x. 5 is probably a mistake for ‘egel.

